The paper deals with the complexity of families of symmetric linear programs (LPs) that decide a property of graphs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graphs and their properties, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of Boolean circuits and fixed-point logic also indicates a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
